This is exactly how it works, otherwise my baby {{champion:75}} **Nasus** wouldn't get any effect from his passive, **Soul Eater**, without purchasing AD.

Lifesteal takes the total *physical* damage dealt ***after*** mitigations, and heals for a percentage of *that*.

To put it simply:

* Physical damage done on an auto attack heals you via lifesteal.
 * This can be amplified by items that deal on-hit physical damage. {{item:3057}} {{item:3153}} {{item:3042}} 
* Magical damage done on an auto attack doesn't heal you via lifesteal.
 * There is one exception to this rule: {{champion:42}}
 * This stops crazy synergy on hybrids. {{item:3100}} {{item:3072}}
* Reducing the physical damage taken, reduces their resulting healing from lifesteal/spellvamp.
 * Overall, mitigating damage in League is deceptively powerful. {{item:1029}} {{item:3047}}  {{item:3812}} {{item:3046}}

